ClerkNPCFacts:
    type: data
    1:
        text: "the 10th president of Fyndalin, Haldor Miekenson, had an unusual obsession with wild foxes. /w/Towards the end of his half-term in office, he had adopted over 50 foxes and kept them as pets. /w/Things got so out of hand that the office of the presidency had to hire a team of specialists to oversee the growing number of foxes he repeatedly returned with after hunting trips."
        lib_ref: 500.6.1/1
    2:
        text: "in 1510, an expedition departed Fyndalin to the distant continent of Nova Marca. /w/Aboard it were almost 300 colonists, hand-picked by then-emperor Ferdinand IX. Upon reaching the colony site, a town named Nyterra was set up and achieved a number of successful yields. /w/Eager, to alert the Emperor, the captain of the expedition travelled back to Fyndalin to deliver the good news. /w/Upon returning to the colony, he realized that all of the colonists had disappeared without a trace, along with the entire town. /w/Until today, historians have no clue what became of the colonists"
        lib_ref: 500.1.2/1